@node play "The game: Installation/Playing"

                             Installation

  The installation is very simple, just place "HoloH" where you
want on your hard drive, floppy disk, Ram Disk, etc. No other files
or Libraries are needed. The only requirement is that your Workbench
must have at least 8 colours.

                             How to play?

  Gameplay is simple: click on the arrows, represented by the
triangular buttons that are located on the edges of the board.
Depending on the direction an arrow is pointing, the coloured shapes
will move in that direction. You can also use the numbered keys on
the numeric keypad to move the coloured shapes in the same way, as
shown below:

        7         8        9
    upper left   up    upper right

        4                  6
      left               right

        1         2        3
    lower left  down   lower right

  If a shape is located on the same edge(s) as the clicked arrow,
that shape will not move... and may block other shapes that are
located next to it.

  You get 1 point for each different shape that fall in the center
hole. The number of points gets doubled every time shapes of the
same type fall consecutively in the hole.

  Each time you move the shapes and none of them fall in the hole,
a new shape will appear at an opposite edge.

  One important thing to remember: do NOT move shapes of the same
type next to each other, either horizontally or vertically, as
they will 'blow up' and that will end the game.

  If you clear up the board, meaning that there are no remaining
coloured shapes, the game will end, and your final score will be
doubled.

  Have fun!

